<cb rend="vertical"/>
<ab>
<lb rend="center"/><persName><choice><abbr>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>Reverend</expan></choice> J. Dyke</persName>
<lb rend="center"/>at <placeName><geogName>Thaba Bossiu</geogName></placeName>
<lb rend="center"/>Care of <persName><choice><abbr>Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>Reverend</expan></choice> J. Alkinson</persName>
<lb rend="center"/><placeName><settlement type="town">Colesberg</settlement></placeName>
</ab> 

	<pb facs="liv_002686_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Please accept my hearty thanks for your
<lb/>sketch of the locality where you are stationed
<lb/>There are many interesting questions connected with
<lb/>it &amp; every other part of the country &amp; which if
<lb/>our other duties would allow one would have
<lb/>much pleasure in investigating. How different
<lb/>from what it once was &amp; How pleasant
<lb/>when noble rivers everywhere rolled on their
<lb/>waters to the sea or inland lakes Last year I
<lb/>followed the course of one for nearly <measure>40 miles</measure>
<lb/>It must have been a spacious river &amp; at the
<lb/>point of junction with a lake I discovered
<lb/>what might have been expected, a <unclear cert="medium">mou<gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="blot"/><supplied>nd</supplied></unclear> 
<lb/><unclear cert="medium"><gap extent="2" unit="chars"/><supplied cert="high">of</supplied></unclear> fluvial deposit, consisting of Tuff  <gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="blot"/>
<lb/>well consolidated &amp; containing a heap of
<lb/>fossils in a beautiful state of preservation
<lb/>They were standing out on the face of the rock
<lb/>in relief &amp; the teeth of the animal (apparently
<lb/>a kind of large <term type="animal">antelope</term>) were so perfect one
<lb/>could hardly conceive they were <del type="strikethrough"><unclear cert="medium">hon</unclear></del> stone
<lb/>The radiated structure of the enamel was <unclear>quite</unclear>
<lb/><unclear>&amp;</unclear> apparent when broken &amp; the little orifice 
<lb/>for the transmission of the nerve &amp; blood <unclear cert="low">venels</unclear>
<lb/>was perfectly <unclear cert="low">patent</unclear> &amp; even the <unclear cert="low">taitas</unclear> on
<lb/>the outside which in <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">herbivorous</add> animals is usually dark
<lb/>coloured was as natural as in <unclear cert="medium">the</unclear> recent
<lb/>subjects. </p> <closer>Mr &amp; Mrs Leinne's affectionate regards to you &amp;c
<lb/><signed><persName><choice><abbr>D</abbr><expan>David</expan></choice> <choice><orig>Liv<gap extent="3" unit="chars" agent="hole"/><supplied>ing</supplied>ston</orig><reg>Livingstone</reg></choice></persName></signed>
</closer>


